<item>
            <title>[LU-19940] sanity 300ug incorrect mdt hash send over wire</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19940</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;239704.000006&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: == sanity test 300ug: migrate overstriped dirs =========== 12:09:00 (1772442540)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;239706.223267&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; LustreError: 224916:0:(mdt_xattr.c:419:mdt_dir_layout_update()) lustre-MDT0000: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x200000404:0x3:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; migrate mdt hash mismatch 83000003 != 3000044&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;239706.617796&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: sanity test_300ug: @@@@@@ FAIL: (2)stripe_count is 22, expect 20&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;239716.923004&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: == sanity test complete, duration 112 sec ================ 12:09:13 (1772442553)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this fail caused a reusing an lsa_pattern field for a mdt hash usage, but overstripe mark failed a check. lets use a separate field for the mdt hash&lt;/p&gt;</description>
